	   <a name=101430627535546></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101430627535546><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Hm..  The perpetual question..</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 21st 10:45 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Dalantia,<br><br>Let me say that I enjoy your posts regularly!<br><br>I wouldn't recommend Ro Armor &quot;en masse&quot; at level 40.&nbsp;&nbsp;The AC on Ry'gorr is pretty close to that of Ro Armor so I'm not sure you would gain much in the way of AC points. You would pick up a few saves, but not much on AC.<br><br>The mix and match concept is probably the best option for now.  I can remember when I went through what I called my &quot;ugly&quot; stages! :)<br><br>I had all Fine Plate and I looked cool.  I replaced that with Ro Armor and I still looked cool and since Ro Armor looks like Fine Plate when worn, it all matched as I added pieces!  But then, about in my 40's where you are now, I began picking up odd armor pieces here and there that I wanted to use.  Pretty soon I had a mixed mess of armor that was better in AC and stats, but looked awful! Oh well, such is life.<br><br>The Deepwater Armor is a great choice for AC. It is a BIG jump over other armors. You won't be able to use any of the right clicky effects until you are 45 (?) but definitely look into a DW Helm as soon as possible, just for the AC if you can't use the clicky effect yet. If you solo a lot like you say, there won't be a more valuable piece of armor you can own IMO.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
